      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Installation and Basic Usage"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# pip install ragas datasets langchain-openai\nfrom ragas import evaluate\nfrom ragas.metrics import (\n    faithfulness,\n    answer_relevancy,\n    context_precision,\n    context_recall,\n)\nfrom datasets import Dataset\n\n# RAGAS expects a Hugging Face Dataset with these columns\ndata = {\n    'question': [\n        'What is the boiling point of water at sea level?',\n    ],\n    'answer': [\n        'Water boils at 100 degrees Celsius (212\u00b0F) at sea level.',\n    ],\n    'contexts': [\n        # List of retrieved passage strings (one list per question)\n        ['Water boils at 100\u00b0C (212\u00b0F) at standard atmospheric pressure (1 atm).'],\n    ],\n    'ground_truth': [\n        # Only needed for context_recall\n        '100 degrees Celsius',\n    ],\n}\n\ndataset = Dataset.from_dict(data)\nresult = evaluate(\n    dataset,\n    metrics=[faithfulness, answer_relevancy, context_precision, context_recall],\n)\nprint(result)\n# {'faithfulness': 1.0, 'answer_relevancy': 0.96,\n#  'context_precision': 1.0, 'context_recall': 1.0}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How Each Metric Works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Faithfulness"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Faithfulness measures whether all claims in the answer are supported by the retrieved context. RAGAS internally decomposes the answer into atomic statements, then prompts the LLM to check each against the context:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Faithfulness = |supported statements| / |total statements|\n#\n# Internal steps (simplified):\n# 1. Extract statements from answer:\n#    'Water boils at 100\u00b0C' \u2192 statements = ['Water boils at 100\u00b0C']\n# 2. For each statement, ask: 'Is this supported by the context?'\n# 3. faithfulness = sum(supported) / len(statements)\n\n# A faithfulness of 1.0 means every claim in the answer\n# can be traced to the retrieved context.\n# A faithfulness of 0.5 means half the claims are hallucinated."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Answer Relevancy"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Answer Relevancy measures whether the answer actually addresses the question. RAGAS uses an indirect approach: it generates "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "hypothetical questions",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " from the answer, then measures how similar those generated questions are to the original \u2014 a high similarity means the answer is on-topic:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Answer Relevancy internal logic (simplified):\n#\n# 1. Given: answer = 'Water boils at 100\u00b0C at sea level.'\n# 2. Generate N questions the answer could be responding to:\n#    - 'What is the boiling point of water?'\n#    - 'At what temperature does water become steam?'\n# 3. Embed each generated question and the original question.\n# 4. answer_relevancy = mean cosine similarity(\n#        embed(original_question), embed(generated_questions)\n#    )\n#\n# Score close to 1.0 = answer directly addresses the question.\n# Score near 0 = answer is off-topic (common for verbose, meandering answers)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Context Precision"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Context Precision checks whether the retrieved passages are actually relevant to the question. It uses a rank-aware precision: passages that are relevant and appear higher in the ranked list contribute more to the score:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Context Precision = \u03a3 (precision@k \u00d7 rel_k) / |relevant passages|\n#\n# Example with 3 retrieved passages:\n# Passage 1: relevant (about boiling point)   \u2192 rel_1 = 1\n# Passage 2: not relevant (about freezing)    \u2192 rel_2 = 0\n# Passage 3: relevant (about altitude effect) \u2192 rel_3 = 1\n#\n# precision@1 = 1/1 = 1.0  (1 relevant in top 1)\n# precision@3 = 2/3 = 0.67 (2 relevant in top 3)\n#\n# Context Precision = (1.0 \u00d7 1 + 0.67 \u00d7 1) / 2 = 0.835\n#\n# A score of 1.0 means all relevant passages appear at the top.\n# A score near 0 means relevant passages are buried under irrelevant ones."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Context Recall"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Context Recall measures how much of the information needed to produce the ground-truth answer is actually present in the retrieved context. It requires a ground-truth answer to use as a reference:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Context Recall = |ground truth claims supported by context| / |ground truth claims|\n#\n# Internal steps:\n# 1. Decompose ground truth into atomic claims:\n#    'Water boils at 100\u00b0C' \u2192 ['boiling point is 100\u00b0C']\n# 2. For each claim: can this be inferred from the context?\n# 3. context_recall = supported_claims / total_claims\n#\n# If context_recall = 0.5: the retriever only surfaced half the\n# information needed to fully answer the question."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Evaluating a Full RAG Pipeline"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI, OpenAIEmbeddings\nfrom langchain_community.vectorstores import FAISS\nfrom langchain.chains import RetrievalQA\nfrom ragas import evaluate\nfrom ragas.metrics import faithfulness, answer_relevancy, context_precision\nfrom datasets import Dataset\n\n# Build a small vector store\ndocs = [\n    'Water boils at 100\u00b0C (212\u00b0F) at standard atmospheric pressure.',\n    'At higher altitudes, lower air pressure causes water to boil below 100\u00b0C.',\n    'The freezing point of water is 0\u00b0C (32\u00b0F).',\n]\nembeddings = OpenAIEmbeddings()\nvectorstore = FAISS.from_texts(docs, embeddings)\n\n# Build RAG chain\nllm = ChatOpenAI(model='gpt-4o-mini', temperature=0)\nqa_chain = RetrievalQA.from_chain_type(\n    llm=llm,\n    retriever=vectorstore.as_retriever(search_kwargs={'k': 2}),\n    return_source_documents=True,\n)\n\n# Run queries and collect data for RAGAS\nquestions = ['What temperature does water boil at?']\nanswers, contexts = [], []\n\nfor q in questions:\n    result = qa_chain({'query': q})\n    answers.append(result['result'])\n    contexts.append([doc.page_content for doc in result['source_documents']])\n\n# Evaluate with RAGAS\ndataset = Dataset.from_dict({\n    'question': questions,\n    'answer': answers,\n    'contexts': contexts,\n})\nresult = evaluate(dataset, metrics=[faithfulness, answer_relevancy, context_precision])\nprint(result.to_pandas())"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Configuring the Judge Model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "By default RAGAS uses gpt-4 as the judge. You can swap in any OpenAI-compatible model or use a local model via a custom LangChain wrapper:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from ragas import evaluate\nfrom ragas.metrics import faithfulness\nfrom langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI, OpenAIEmbeddings\nfrom ragas.llms import LangchainLLMWrapper\nfrom ragas.embeddings import LangchainEmbeddingsWrapper\n\n# Use a cheaper / different judge model\njudge_llm = LangchainLLMWrapper(ChatOpenAI(model='gpt-4o-mini'))\njudge_emb = LangchainEmbeddingsWrapper(OpenAIEmbeddings())\n\n# Assign to specific metrics\nfaithfulness.llm = judge_llm\n\n# Or configure globally\nfrom ragas.run_config import RunConfig\nrun_config = RunConfig(max_workers=4, timeout=60)\n\nresult = evaluate(\n    dataset,\n    metrics=[faithfulness],\n    llm=judge_llm,\n    embeddings=judge_emb,\n    run_config=run_config,\n)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Custom Metrics"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "RAGAS provides a base class for writing custom metrics. A custom metric must implement "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "name",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "evaluation_mode",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "_ascore",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (async score):"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from ragas.metrics.base import Metric, EvaluationMode\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nimport asyncio\n\n@dataclass\nclass ResponseLength(Metric):\n    \"\"\"Penalizes overly long answers. Max words: 100.\"\"\"\n    name: str = 'response_length'\n    evaluation_mode: EvaluationMode = EvaluationMode.qa\n    max_words: int = 100\n\n    def init(self, run_config):\n        pass  # no LLM needed for this metric\n\n    async def _ascore(self, row: dict, callbacks=None) -> float:\n        answer = row.get('answer', '')\n        word_count = len(answer.split())\n        # 1.0 if short enough, degrades linearly to 0 at 2\u00d7 limit\n        score = max(0.0, 1.0 - max(0, word_count - self.max_words) / self.max_words)\n        return score\n\nlength_metric = ResponseLength(max_words=80)\nresult = evaluate(dataset, metrics=[faithfulness, length_metric])\nprint(result)"
          }
        ]
      },
